The '''rule consciousness''' as one of the primary factors of [[personality]] out of sixteen was categorized by (Raymond Cattell, 1946) as low and high level. The descriptors of low level rule consciousness are expedient, nonconforming, disregards rules, self-indulgent or having a low [[super ego]] strength while the high level consciousness are rule-conscious, dutiful, conscientious, conforming, moralistic, staid, rule bound or having high super ego strength.
